    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-28T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-28T01:00:00-05:00" n="98"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3707: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-28T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 28, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 28—4:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I learn on reliable authority that the Japanese military authorities intend to
                    take action tomorrow morning January 29th. This is confirmed <pb facs="0188"
                        n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/> by Secretary General of Council who was asked by
                    Japanese [Consul General?] whether in event of prolonged Japanese occupation of
                    Chinese territory contiguous to Settlement, Settlement police would undertake
                    policing thereof. Japanese Admiral has waived his rights as senior officer in
                    connection with Settlement deference [<hi rend="italic">defense?</hi>] and
                    Brigadier <persName corresp="#p_FLW1">Franklin</persName> [<persName
                        corresp="#p_FBG1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fleming</hi>
                    </persName>], British commander, is senior officer. Later. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DWH1">Donald</persName> has just informed me that the Mayor’s
                    reply will be delivered to Japanese today [and] will be an unqualified
                    acceptance of Japanese demands.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
